CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778839649
OL,3,CPeston: Starmer has handed his future
OL,4,Cto Burnham
OL,6,FThis is both Burnham and Starmer
OL,7,Fgenuinely rolling the dice.
OL,9,FThat's not just because Burnham is way
OL,10,Fmore popular than Starmer among Labour
OL,11,Fmembers and trade union leaders, and
OL,12,Fprobably more popular among MPs too.
OL,14,FIt's because Burnham and his fans
OL,15,Fcharacterise him as the answer to
OL,16,FFarage and Reform. And on the basis of
OL,17,Flast week's local election results,
OL,18,FMakerfield is now a Reform heartland,
OL,19,Fhaving previously been part of the
OL,20,FLabour Red Wall.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778839649
OL,3,CPeston: Starmer has handed his future
OL,4,Cto Burnham
OL,6,FSo if Burnham loses, maybe he's not
OL,7,Fthe answer to all Labour's woes, and
OL,8,FStarmer survives - possibly even to
OL,9,Ffight the next election (though his
OL,10,Fcritics believe Streeting and Rayner
OL,11,Fwould precipitate a leadership
OL,12,Felection even after a Burnham defeat).
OL,14,FBut if Burnham wins, Starmer should
OL,15,Fbook the removal vans as soon as the
OL,16,FMakerfield count is over. Because
OL,17,Fthose members, MPs and trade union
OL,18,Fleaders would carry Burnham shoulder-
OL,19,Fhigh into Number 10, and Starmer would
OL,20,Fbe binned.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
